events.description: Pepin of Herstal, mayor of the Merovingian palace, dies at Jupille (modern Belgium). He is succeeded by his infant grandson Theudoald, while his widow Plectrude holds actual power in the Frankish Kingdom.
events.html: • 714 – Pepin of Herstal, mayor of the Merovingian palace, dies at Jupille (modern Belgium). He is succeeded by his infant grandson Theudoald, while his widow Plectrude holds actual power in the Frankish Kingdom.[1]

events.description: An Lushan revolts against Chancellor Yang Guozhong at Yanjing, initiating the An Lushan Rebellion during the Tang dynasty of China.
events.html: • 755 – An Lushan revolts against Chancellor Yang Guozhong at Yanjing, initiating the An Lushan Rebellion during the Tang dynasty of China.[2]

events.description: Hundred Years' War: Henry VI of England is crowned King of France at Notre Dame in Paris.
events.html: • 1431 – Hundred Years' War: Henry VI of England is crowned King of France at Notre Dame in Paris.[3]

events.description: Vasco da Gama passes the Great Fish River at the southern tip of Africa, where Bartolomeu Dias had previously turned back to Portugal.
events.html: • 1497 – Vasco da Gama passes the Great Fish River at the southern tip of Africa, where Bartolomeu Dias had previously turned back to Portugal.[4]

events.description: An earthquake with an estimated magnitude of 8.5Mw  strikes Valdivia, Chile.
events.html: • 1575 – An earthquake with an estimated magnitude of 8.5Mw  strikes Valdivia, Chile.[5]

events.description: Seven-Year War: Battle of Noryang: The final battle of the Seven-Year War is fought between the China and the Korean allied forces and Japanese navies, resulting in a decisive allied forces victory.
events.html: • 1598 – Seven-Year War: Battle of Noryang: The final battle of the Seven-Year War is fought between the China and the Korean allied forces and Japanese navies, resulting in a decisive allied forces victory.[6]

events.description: English Interregnum: The Protectorate: Oliver Cromwell becomes Lord Protector of the Commonwealth of England, Scotland and Ireland.
events.html: • 1653 – English Interregnum: The Protectorate: Oliver Cromwell becomes Lord Protector of the Commonwealth of England, Scotland and Ireland.

events.description: Convention Parliament: The Declaration of Right is embodied in the Bill of Rights.
events.html: • 1689 – Convention Parliament: The Declaration of Right is embodied in the Bill of Rights.

events.description: Most Recent Eruption of Mount Fuji.
events.html: • 1707 – Most Recent Eruption of Mount Fuji.[7]

events.description: Seven Years' War: After a four-month siege, the Russians under Pyotr Rumyantsev take the Prussian fortress of Kołobrzeg.
events.html: • 1761 – Seven Years' War: After a four-month siege, the Russians under Pyotr Rumyantsev take the Prussian fortress of Kołobrzeg.

events.description: American Revolution: Boston Tea Party: Members of the Sons of Liberty disguised as Mohawk Indians dump hundreds of crates of tea into Boston harbor as a protest against the Tea Act.
events.html: • 1773 – American Revolution: Boston Tea Party: Members of the Sons of Liberty disguised as Mohawk Indians dump hundreds of crates of tea into Boston harbor as a protest against the Tea Act.

events.description: Virginia becomes the first state to ratify the Articles of Confederation.
events.html: • 1777 – Virginia becomes the first state to ratify the Articles of Confederation. [1]

events.description: British East India Company: Muharram Rebellion: Hada and Mada Miah lead the first anti-British uprising in the subcontinent against Robert Lindsay and his contingents in Sylhet Shahi Eidgah.
events.html: • 1782 – British East India Company: Muharram Rebellion: Hada and Mada Miah lead the first anti-British uprising in the subcontinent against Robert Lindsay and his contingents in Sylhet Shahi Eidgah.[8]

events.description: The first two in a series of four severe earthquakes occur in the vicinity of New Madrid, Missouri.
events.html: • 1811 – The first two in a series of four severe earthquakes occur in the vicinity of New Madrid, Missouri.

events.description: Benjamin W. Edwards rides into Mexican-controlled Nacogdoches, Texas, and declares himself ruler of the Republic of Fredonia.
events.html: • 1826 – Benjamin W. Edwards rides into Mexican-controlled Nacogdoches, Texas, and declares himself ruler of the Republic of Fredonia.

events.description: Great Trek: Battle of Blood River: Voortrekkers led by Andries Pretorius and Sarel Cilliers defeat Zulu impis, led by Dambuza (Nzobo) and Ndlela kaSompisi in what is today KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa.
events.html: • 1838 – Great Trek: Battle of Blood River: Voortrekkers led by Andries Pretorius and Sarel Cilliers defeat Zulu impis, led by Dambuza (Nzobo) and Ndlela kaSompisi in what is today KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa.[9]

events.description: The Charlotte Jane and the Randolph bring the first of the Canterbury Pilgrims to Lyttelton, New Zealand.
events.html: • 1850 – The Charlotte Jane and the Randolph bring the first of the Canterbury Pilgrims to Lyttelton, New Zealand.

events.description: American Civil War: Joseph E. Johnston replaces Braxton Bragg as commander of the Confederate Army of Tennessee.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: Joseph E. Johnston replaces Braxton Bragg as commander of the Confederate Army of Tennessee.

events.description: American Civil War: Battle of Nashville: The Union's Army of the Cumberland routs and destroys the Confederacy's Army of Tennessee, ending its effectiveness as a combat unit.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: Battle of Nashville: The Union's Army of the Cumberland routs and destroys the Confederacy's Army of Tennessee, ending its effectiveness as a combat unit.

events.description: Outbreak of the First Boer War between the Boer South African Republic and the British Empire.
events.html: • 1880 – Outbreak of the First Boer War between the Boer South African Republic and the British Empire.

events.description: Wales and England contest the first Home Nations (now Six Nations) rugby union match.
events.html: • 1882 – Wales and England contest the first Home Nations (now Six Nations) rugby union match.

events.description: Tonkin Campaign: French forces capture the Sơn Tây citadel.
events.html: • 1883 – Tonkin Campaign: French forces capture the Sơn Tây citadel.

events.description: In Rugby Union, The "Match of the Century" is played between Wales and New Zealand at Cardiff Arms Park.
events.html: • 1905 – In Rugby Union, The "Match of the Century" is played between Wales and New Zealand at Cardiff Arms Park.[10][11]

entities.name: New Zealand national rugby union team

events.description: First Balkan War: The Royal Hellenic Navy defeats the Ottoman Navy at the Battle of Elli.
events.html: • 1912 – First Balkan War: The Royal Hellenic Navy defeats the Ottoman Navy at the Battle of Elli.

events.description: World War I: Admiral Franz von Hipper commands a raid on Scarborough, Hartlepool and Whitby.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: Admiral Franz von Hipper commands a raid on Scarborough, Hartlepool and Whitby.

entities.name: Raid on Scarborough, Hartlepool and Whitby

events.description: The Haiyuan earthquake of 8.5Mw , rocks the Gansu province in China, killing an estimated 200,000.
events.html: • 1920 – The Haiyuan earthquake of 8.5Mw , rocks the Gansu province in China, killing an estimated 200,000.

events.description: The Holocaust: Schutzstaffel chief Heinrich Himmler orders that Roma candidates for extermination be deported to Auschwitz.
events.html: • 1942 – The Holocaust: Schutzstaffel chief Heinrich Himmler orders that Roma candidates for extermination be deported to Auschwitz.

events.description: World War II: The Battle of the Bulge begins with the surprise offensive of three German armies through the Ardennes forest.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Battle of the Bulge begins with the surprise offensive of three German armies through the Ardennes forest.

events.description: A Miami Airlines Curtiss C-46 Commando crashes in Elizabeth, New Jersey, killing all 58 aboard including dancer Doris Ruby.
events.html: • 1951 – A Miami Airlines Curtiss C-46 Commando crashes in Elizabeth, New Jersey, killing all 58 aboard including dancer Doris Ruby.[12]

events.description: A United Airlines Douglas DC-8 and a TWA Lockheed Super Constellation collide over Staten Island, New York and crash, killing all 128 people aboard both aircraft and six more on the ground.
events.html: • 1960 – A United Airlines Douglas DC-8 and a TWA Lockheed Super Constellation collide over Staten Island, New York and crash, killing all 128 people aboard both aircraft and six more on the ground.

events.description: Second Vatican Council: Official revocation of the Edict of Expulsion of Jews from Spain.
events.html: • 1968 – Second Vatican Council: Official revocation of the Edict of Expulsion of Jews from Spain.[13]

events.description: Bangladesh Liberation War and Indo-Pakistani War of 1971: The Surrender of the Pakistan Army brings an end to both conflicts. This is commemorated annually as Victory Day in Bangladesh and India respectively.
events.html: • 1971 – Bangladesh Liberation War and Indo-Pakistani War of 1971: The Surrender of the Pakistan Army brings an end to both conflicts. This is commemorated annually as Victory Day in Bangladesh and India respectively.

events.description: The United Kingdom recognizes Bahrain's independence, which is commemorated annually as Bahrain's National Day.
events.html: • 1971 – The United Kingdom recognizes Bahrain's independence, which is commemorated annually as Bahrain's National Day.

events.description: Aeroflot Flight 2022 crashes in the Soviet Union's (now Russia) Volokolamsky District, killing all 51 aboard, including 4 Lithuanian doctors.
events.html: • 1973 – Aeroflot Flight 2022 crashes in the Soviet Union's (now Russia) Volokolamsky District, killing all 51 aboard, including 4 Lithuanian doctors.[14]

events.description: Jeltoqsan: Riots erupt in Alma-Ata, Kazakh SSR, in response to Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev's dismissal of ethnic Kazakh Dinmukhamed Kunaev, the First Secretary of the Communist Party of Kazakhstan, and his replacement with Gennady Kolbin, an ethnic Russian from the Russian SFSR.
events.html: • 1986 – Jeltoqsan: Riots erupt in Alma-Ata, Kazakh SSR, in response to Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev's dismissal of ethnic Kazakh Dinmukhamed Kunaev, the First Secretary of the Communist Party of Kazakhstan, and his replacement with Gennady Kolbin, an ethnic Russian from the Russian SFSR.[15]

events.description: Romanian Revolution: Protests break out in Timișoara, Romania, in response to an attempt by the government to evict dissident Hungarian pastor László Tőkés.
events.html: • 1989 – Romanian Revolution: Protests break out in Timișoara, Romania, in response to an attempt by the government to evict dissident Hungarian pastor László Tőkés.

events.description: Zhanaozen massacre: Violent protests by oil workers take place in Zhanaozen, Kazakhstan, leading to 16 people dead and 100 injured by the security forces.
events.html: • 2011 – Zhanaozen massacre: Violent protests by oil workers take place in Zhanaozen, Kazakhstan, leading to 16 people dead and 100 injured by the security forces.[16]

events.description: A bus falls from an elevated highway in the Philippines capital Manila killing at least 18 people with 20 injured.
events.html: • 2013 – A bus falls from an elevated highway in the Philippines capital Manila killing at least 18 people with 20 injured.

events.description: Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan militants attack an Army Public School in Peshawar, Pakistan, killing 150 people, 132 of them schoolchildren.
events.html: • 2014 – Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan militants attack an Army Public School in Peshawar, Pakistan, killing 150 people, 132 of them schoolchildren.[17]
